criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  ≥ 20years of age;

          -  diagnosis of stroke (>6months);

          -  sedentary or insufficiently active;

          -  have a writing medical permission to participate in the training program.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  cognitive impairment (Mini-Mental Status Examination score: illiterate 13 points;
             elementary and middle school 18 points; and high-school 26 points; or inability to
             respond to verbal command);

          -  inability to walk independently for at least 10 minutes, with or without walking
             devices;

          -  pain or other disorders precluding their participation.
